<p>Im using the rzSlider directive for angularjs and I want to have a label shadow the slider button and display some text associated with the value the button is currently at and I have no idea how to make this happen. Can anyone help? (I am new to this angular thing)</p>  <p>This is the directive in my html and the span for the label I want to shadow the slider button.</p>  <pre><code>    &lt;rzslider rz-slider-model="vm.priceSlider.value" rz-slider-floor="vm.priceSlider" rz-slider-ceil=floor="vm.priceSlider.ceil" rz-slider-on-end="vm.onSliderChange()"&gt;&lt;/rzslider&gt;     &lt;span class="rz-pointer"&gt;{{vm.text}}&lt;/span&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This is the code in the controller</p>  <pre><code>    vm.priceSlider = {         value: 0,         floor: 0,         ceil: 18      }      vm.onSliderChange = function () {         if (vm.priceSlider.value &lt;= 13) {             vm.text = "someval";         }         else if (vm.priceSlider.value &lt;= 16){             vm.text = "someval";         }         else if (vm.priceSlider.value &gt;= 18) {             vm.text = "someval";         }         else {             vm.text = " ";         }       } </code></pre>  <p>so when the slider button slides from lets say 1- 12  i want the text to shadow  the slider button and be shown underneath it.                   </p>